
lunatic ['luːnətɪk] a. n.
Someone behaves in a dangerous, stupid, or annoying way. 疯子

psychotic[saɪ'kɒtɪk] a. n.
Someone who is psychotic has a type of severe mental illness.

fanatic [fə'nætɪk] a. n.
1) If you describe someone as a fanatic, you disapprove of them because you
consider their behaviour or opinions to be very extreme, for example, in the way
they support particular religious or political ideas.
2) If you say that someone is a fanatic, you mean that they are very
enthusiastic about a particular activity, sport, or way of life.
